 By voice teachers in the opera world, this goes by the name of “squillo”, the Italian word for “ring”. %0a%3c %0a%3c The word formant refers to dominant harmonic overtones in a certain phonation that can be visualized on a spectrogram. Formants can be used in acoustic phonetics to determine the quality of a vowel by showing patterns of voicing of different frequencies present in the phonation. It can also be used to determine consonants by showing patterns of frication in different areas. In terms of the singer’s formant, a spectrogram will show the fundamental frequency (in the music world, pitch) of the note and a presence of an additional formant (or sometimes two!) on the next pitches of the harmonic series, layered in octaves above the pitch. Use of the singer’s formant helps the voice to cut through a theatre, instead of straining to project louder than the orchestra in a literal sense. %0a%3c %0a%3c https://www.actorproject.org/tor/timbre-lingo/2019/12/10/the-singers-formant%0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c [[#contentends]]%0a%3c ----%0a%3c ----%0a%3c %0a%3c !!Expansions:%0a%3c [[#expansions]]%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#expansionsend]]%0a%3c %0a%3c ----%0a%3c %25red%25 '''Add an expansion:'''%0a%3c %0a%3c (:if [ exists GradebookExpansions.{$Name}-{$Author} || equal {$Author} {$:Author} ] :)%0a%3c %0a%3c (:else:)%0a%3c %0a%3c (:foxform Site.FoxForms#newexpansion:)%0a%3c %0a%3c (:ifend:)%0a%3c %0a%3c ----%0a%3c ----%0a%3c %0a%3c !!Comments%0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c (:section: E:)%0a%3c (:Category: Varia:)%0a\ No newline at end of file%0a
